President Biden addressed the International Union of Operating Engineers Local 77 in Accokeek, Maryland, expressing his gratitude for their support and highlighting the progress made under his administration. He emphasized the importance of unions and the middle class in building America and called for a fairer economic vision that benefits working people. The President discussed his economic plan, including investments in infrastructure, clean energy, and manufacturing, and stressed the need for corporations and the wealthy to pay their fair share of taxes. He criticized the Republican Party's proposed spending cuts and tax cuts for the wealthy and warned against the possibility of defaulting on the national debt. President Biden concluded by expressing his optimism for America's future and the potential for positive change when working together.